      Sorry, off topic, but pet peeve:<br />The plural 'Winklevii' makes no sense. I'm assuming that the Zuckerberg character was jokingly using the Roman plural 'Winklevi', as if their name was 'Winklevus', rather than 'Winklevoss'. It sounds almost the same, so it's a somewhat cute joke. Using 'Winklevii' would only make sense if their name was 'Winklevioss',  which could be pronounced as 'Winklevius', which would have a Roman plural -ii. <br /><br />Ok, pet peeve silenced and kicked into a corner. Carry on.
      
