    </header>
    <div class="body">
      <div class="quotetitle">ubercurmudgeon wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">So this is what Bitcoins are for: a form of gambling for the idle rich that, unlike stock markets and real currency trading, does not result in the destruction of real, productive industries. Great idea! Phase two will surely be to convince the owners of large Bitcoin hordes to trade them in for places on a &quot;B&quot; ark leaving the solar system.</div><br /><br />No, it's a form of gambling for the mentally ill and libertarians who dream of sticking it to the man when it comes to money.<br /><br />For all of their yelping about how fiat currency is evil, they still have to transfer their buttcoins to some sort of fiat currency to do anything with them outside of using them on SilkRoad.
      
    </div>
    <footer>
